          <mj-text align="left" font-size="16px" line-height="20.5px" padding="15px">
            <h1 style="font-size:21px">The History of Mozart and Da Ponte</h1>
            <p>
              There are so many elements that go into making a classic opera. While a brilliant composer is a must there should also be a gripping story to highlight the genius music. Lorenzo Da Ponte is most famous for being the librettist for three of Mozart's greatest operas (The Marriage of Figaro, Don Giovanni, and Cosi Fan Tutte).
            </p>
            <p>
              Join us as we take a brief look at this pair's fascinating history as well as Da Ponte's influence on Mozart's masterpieces.</p>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-button background-color="#FCDA30" color="#000000" font-weight="bold" font-size="14px" padding="0px" href="https://www.laopera.org/discover/la-opera-content/new-blog-post-44/?utm_source=ActiveCampaign&utm_medium=email&utm_content=Pre-Simulcast+Activities+for+You&utm_campaign=September+22nd+E-Newsletter" alt="The History of Mozart and Da Pointe">
            READ HERE
          </mj-button>
        </mj-column>
